  "texts": [
    "Notice that the taxonomy uses terms as they appear in the articles, albeit often in abbreviated form.",
    "The exception is the term 'cost-aware scheduling' that this study adopted.",
    "As the energy load prediction as such has evolved to scheduling of devices and to taking into account the cost factors, there is a need for defining terminology.",
    "Even though some of the identified articles propose applications to these current aims, they mostly do not articulate this in precise terms.This taxonomy is different from the existing ones, as the taxonomy of some surveys concentrate on a type of machine learning, for instance, neural networks [24], or on an application area of a smart building, for instance building load [30].",
    "Moreover, [27] considers operation, control and retrofit; however, it does not include the human-in-the-loop as such in its taxonomy."
